{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01NexKQGxRmVdUbtyxqrufdk","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information needed. Let me create a comprehensive summary:\n\n## Event Handler Architecture Summary\n\nI've analyzed the backend event system in depth. Here's the complete picture:\n\n### 1. **Event Types & Constants**\n**File:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/event-types.ts`\n\nEvent types are defined as a const object with derived union type:\n```typescript\nexport const EventTypes = {\n  REFERRAL_CODE_APPLIED: \"referral.code_applied\",\n  REFERRAL_GAME_SETTLED: \"referral.game_settled\",\n  REFERRAL_CLAIM_REQUESTED: \"referral.claim_requested\",\n  GAME_SETTLED: \"game.settled\",\n  REWARD_POOL_FUND: \"reward.pool_fund\",\n  POINTS_GRANT: \"points.grant\",\n  CRATE_DROP: \"crate.drop\",\n  CRATE_SOL_PAYOUT: \"crate.sol_payout\",\n} as const;\n\nexport type EventType = (typeof EventTypes)[keyof typeof EventTypes];\n```\n\n### 2. **Emitting Events**\n**File:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/emit-event.ts`\n\nEvents are emitted within database transactions for atomicity:\n```typescript\nexport async function emitEvent(\n  tx: SqlOrTransaction,\n  eventType: EventType,\n  payload: Record<string, unknown>,\n  options?: EmitEventOptions,\n): Promise<{ eventId: bigint }>;\n```\n\n**Usage in settle-tx.ts:**\n```typescript\nawait emitEvent(txDb.rawSql, EventTypes.GAME_SETTLED, {\n  roundId: round.match_id,\n  roundPda: pda,\n  game: \"coinflip\",\n  players: [\n    {\n      userId: creatorUserId ?? creator.toBase58(),\n      wallet: creator.toBase58(),\n      amountLamports: String(entryAmount),\n      isWinner: winner.equals(creator),\n      payoutLamports: winner.equals(creator) ? String(payoutAmount) : \"0\",\n      isCreator: true,\n    },\n    {\n      userId: opponentUserId ?? opponent.toBase58(),\n      wallet: opponent.toBase58(),\n      amountLamports: String(entryAmount),\n      isWinner: winner.equals(opponent),\n      payoutLamports: winner.equals(opponent) ? String(payoutAmount) : \"0\",\n      isCreator: false,\n    },\n  ],\n  feeLamports: String(feeAmount),\n  settledAt: new Date().toISOString(),\n});\n```\n\n### 3. **Handler Registry & Handler Pattern**\n**File:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/handler-registry.ts`\n\n```typescript\nexport type EventHandler = (\n  payload: Record<string, unknown>,\n) => Promise<void>;\n\nexport function registerHandler(\n  eventType: EventType,\n  handler: EventHandler,\n): void {\n  handlers.set(eventType, handler);\n}\n\nexport function getHandler(eventType: string): EventHandler | undefined {\n  return handlers.get(eventType);\n}\n```\n\n### 4. **Handler Registration Pattern**\n**File:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/index.ts` (lines 205-209)\n\nHandlers are registered at startup before the worker starts:\n```typescript\nregisterHandler(\n  EventTypes.REFERRAL_CLAIM_REQUESTED,\n  createClaimHandler({ db, connection, serverKeypair: config.serverKeypair }),\n);\n```\n\n### 5. **Handler Implementation Example**\n**File:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/handlers/referral-claim.ts`\n\nPattern: Factory function that returns an async handler:\n```typescript\nexport interface ClaimHandlerDeps {\n  db: Db;\n  connection: Connection;\n  serverKeypair: Keypair;\n}\n\nexport function createClaimHandler(deps: ClaimHandlerDeps) {\n  const { db, connection, serverKeypair } = deps;\n\n  return async (payload: Record<string, unknown>): Promise<void> => {\n    const claimId = payload.claimId as string;\n    const userId = payload.userId as string;\n    const wallet = payload.wallet as string;\n    const amountLamports = payload.amountLamports as string;\n    // ... implementation\n  };\n}\n```\n\nKey principles:\n- **Idempotent**: Re-processing same event is safe no-op (check DB state first)\n- **Validates payload**: Throw if required fields missing\n- **Error handling**: Transient errors rethrow (retried with backoff), permanent errors mark status 'failed'\n\n### 6. **Event Queue Worker**\n**File:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/worker.ts`\n\n```typescript\nexport function createEventWorker(\n  sql: postgres.Sql,\n  options?: EventWorkerOptions,\n): EventWorker {\n  // Polls event_queue table at configurable interval\n  // Claims events with FOR UPDATE SKIP LOCKED for concurrency\n  // Dispatches to registered handler\n  // Handles retry with exponential backoff: 1→5s, 2→30s, 3+→300s\n  // Status flow: pending → processing → completed|dead|pending(retry)\n}\n```\n\n### 7. **Game.settled Event Payload Shape**\nFrom `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/worker/settle-tx.ts` (coinflip) and integration tests:\n\n```typescript\n{\n  roundId: string;              // match_id from rounds table\n  roundPda: string;             // PDA as base58\n  game: \"coinflip\" | \"lord\" | \"closecall\";\n  players: Array<{\n    userId: string;             // user_id or wallet if no profile\n    wallet: string;             // base58 address\n    amountLamports: string;     // string-encoded lamports (entry amount)\n    isWinner: boolean;\n    payoutLamports: string;     // \"0\" for losers, payout amount for winner\n    isCreator: boolean;         // true for round creator\n  }>;\n  feeLamports: string;          // string-encoded fee amount\n  settledAt: string;            // ISO 8601 timestamp\n}\n```\n\n### 8. **Testing Patterns**\n**Files:**\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/__tests__/queue.test.ts` — Unit tests\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/__tests__/queue-integration.test.ts` — Worker integration\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/__tests__/integration.test.ts` — End-to-end settlement flow\n\nKey patterns:\n- Clear handlers with `clearHandlers()` between tests\n- Truncate event_queue table before each test\n- Use `waitFor()` to poll for handler execution\n- Verify DB status transitions and payload content\n\n### 9. **Database Schema**\n**File:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/migrations/009_event_queue.sql`\n\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE event_queue (\n  id            BIGINT GENERATED ALWAYS AS IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY,\n  event_type    TEXT         NOT NULL,\n  payload       JSONB        NOT NULL,\n  status        TEXT         NOT NULL DEFAULT 'pending' \n                CHECK (status IN ('pending', 'processing', 'completed', 'failed', 'dead')),\n  attempts      INTEGER      NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n  max_attempts  INTEGER      NOT NULL DEFAULT 3,\n  scheduled_at  TIMESTAMPTZ  NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),\n  started_at    TIMESTAMPTZ,\n  completed_at  TIMESTAMPTZ,\n  error         TEXT,\n  created_at    TIMESTAMPTZ  NOT NULL DEFAULT now()\n);\n```\n\n---\n\n### To Register a New Handler:\n\n1. **Add event type** to `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/event-types.ts`\n2. **Create handler file** (e.g., `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/handlers/my-handler.ts`) with factory function pattern\n3. **Register in index.ts** (line ~206) before worker starts\n4. **Emit events** from settlement code using `emitEvent(txDb.rawSql, EventTypes.MY_EVENT, payload)`\n5. **Test** using queue integration test pattern with handler mocking and DB assertions"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f10eba72-1ffd-4ead-a08a-c9ca057b30d5","uuid":"4b49f125-07bb-44c0-9e1e-f7f5efe4a419","timestamp":"2026-04-03T19:29:43.111Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"In /workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/, find:\n1. How event handlers are registered — look for a handler registry, handler map, or event dispatch pattern\n2. The emitEvent function — how events are emitted and what their shape is\n3. The settle-tx.ts file — specifically the game.settled event emission added in iteration 1 to understand the payload shape\n4. Any existing test files (especially integration.test.ts) to understand the testing pattern\n\nI need to understand the exact types used for event payloads and how to register a new handler.","agentId":"aae7f65d07194ee37","agentType":"Explore","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information needed. Let me create a comprehensive summary:\n\n## Event Handler Architecture Summary\n\nI've analyzed the backend event system in depth. Here's the complete picture:\n\n### 1. **Event Types & Constants**\n**File:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/event-types.ts`\n\nEvent types are defined as a const object with derived union type:\n```typescript\nexport const EventTypes = {\n  REFERRAL_CODE_APPLIED: \"referral.code_applied\",\n  REFERRAL_GAME_SETTLED: \"referral.game_settled\",\n  REFERRAL_CLAIM_REQUESTED: \"referral.claim_requested\",\n  GAME_SETTLED: \"game.settled\",\n  REWARD_POOL_FUND: \"reward.pool_fund\",\n  POINTS_GRANT: \"points.grant\",\n  CRATE_DROP: \"crate.drop\",\n  CRATE_SOL_PAYOUT: \"crate.sol_payout\",\n} as const;\n\nexport type EventType = (typeof EventTypes)[keyof typeof EventTypes];\n```\n\n### 2. **Emitting Events**\n**File:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/emit-event.ts`\n\nEvents are emitted within database transactions for atomicity:\n```typescript\nexport async function emitEvent(\n  tx: SqlOrTransaction,\n  eventType: EventType,\n  payload: Record<string, unknown>,\n  options?: EmitEventOptions,\n): Promise<{ eventId: bigint }>;\n```\n\n**Usage in settle-tx.ts:**\n```typescript\nawait emitEvent(txDb.rawSql, EventTypes.GAME_SETTLED, {\n  roundId: round.match_id,\n  roundPda: pda,\n  game: \"coinflip\",\n  players: [\n    {\n      userId: creatorUserId ?? creator.toBase58(),\n      wallet: creator.toBase58(),\n      amountLamports: String(entryAmount),\n      isWinner: winner.equals(creator),\n      payoutLamports: winner.equals(creator) ? String(payoutAmount) : \"0\",\n      isCreator: true,\n    },\n    {\n      userId: opponentUserId ?? opponent.toBase58(),\n      wallet: opponent.toBase58(),\n      amountLamports: String(entryAmount),\n      isWinner: winner.equals(opponent),\n      payoutLamports: winner.equals(opponent) ? String(payoutAmount) : \"0\",\n      isCreator: false,\n    },\n  ],\n  feeLamports: String(feeAmount),\n  settledAt: new Date().toISOString(),\n});\n```\n\n### 3. **Handler Registry & Handler Pattern**\n**File:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/handler-registry.ts`\n\n```typescript\nexport type EventHandler = (\n  payload: Record<string, unknown>,\n) => Promise<void>;\n\nexport function registerHandler(\n  eventType: EventType,\n  handler: EventHandler,\n): void {\n  handlers.set(eventType, handler);\n}\n\nexport function getHandler(eventType: string): EventHandler | undefined {\n  return handlers.get(eventType);\n}\n```\n\n### 4. **Handler Registration Pattern**\n**File:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/index.ts` (lines 205-209)\n\nHandlers are registered at startup before the worker starts:\n```typescript\nregisterHandler(\n  EventTypes.REFERRAL_CLAIM_REQUESTED,\n  createClaimHandler({ db, connection, serverKeypair: config.serverKeypair }),\n);\n```\n\n### 5. **Handler Implementation Example**\n**File:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/handlers/referral-claim.ts`\n\nPattern: Factory function that returns an async handler:\n```typescript\nexport interface ClaimHandlerDeps {\n  db: Db;\n  connection: Connection;\n  serverKeypair: Keypair;\n}\n\nexport function createClaimHandler(deps: ClaimHandlerDeps) {\n  const { db, connection, serverKeypair } = deps;\n\n  return async (payload: Record<string, unknown>): Promise<void> => {\n    const claimId = payload.claimId as string;\n    const userId = payload.userId as string;\n    const wallet = payload.wallet as string;\n    const amountLamports = payload.amountLamports as string;\n    // ... implementation\n  };\n}\n```\n\nKey principles:\n- **Idempotent**: Re-processing same event is safe no-op (check DB state first)\n- **Validates payload**: Throw if required fields missing\n- **Error handling**: Transient errors rethrow (retried with backoff), permanent errors mark status 'failed'\n\n### 6. **Event Queue Worker**\n**File:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/worker.ts`\n\n```typescript\nexport function createEventWorker(\n  sql: postgres.Sql,\n  options?: EventWorkerOptions,\n): EventWorker {\n  // Polls event_queue table at configurable interval\n  // Claims events with FOR UPDATE SKIP LOCKED for concurrency\n  // Dispatches to registered handler\n  // Handles retry with exponential backoff: 1→5s, 2→30s, 3+→300s\n  // Status flow: pending → processing → completed|dead|pending(retry)\n}\n```\n\n### 7. **Game.settled Event Payload Shape**\nFrom `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/worker/settle-tx.ts` (coinflip) and integration tests:\n\n```typescript\n{\n  roundId: string;              // match_id from rounds table\n  roundPda: string;             // PDA as base58\n  game: \"coinflip\" | \"lord\" | \"closecall\";\n  players: Array<{\n    userId: string;             // user_id or wallet if no profile\n    wallet: string;             // base58 address\n    amountLamports: string;     // string-encoded lamports (entry amount)\n    isWinner: boolean;\n    payoutLamports: string;     // \"0\" for losers, payout amount for winner\n    isCreator: boolean;         // true for round creator\n  }>;\n  feeLamports: string;          // string-encoded fee amount\n  settledAt: string;            // ISO 8601 timestamp\n}\n```\n\n### 8. **Testing Patterns**\n**Files:**\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/__tests__/queue.test.ts` — Unit tests\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/__tests__/queue-integration.test.ts` — Worker integration\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/__tests__/integration.test.ts` — End-to-end settlement flow\n\nKey patterns:\n- Clear handlers with `clearHandlers()` between tests\n- Truncate event_queue table before each test\n- Use `waitFor()` to poll for handler execution\n- Verify DB status transitions and payload content\n\n### 9. **Database Schema**\n**File:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/migrations/009_event_queue.sql`\n\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE event_queue (\n  id            BIGINT GENERATED ALWAYS AS IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY,\n  event_type    TEXT         NOT NULL,\n  payload       JSONB        NOT NULL,\n  status        TEXT         NOT NULL DEFAULT 'pending' \n                CHECK (status IN ('pending', 'processing', 'completed', 'failed', 'dead')),\n  attempts      INTEGER      NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n  max_attempts  INTEGER      NOT NULL DEFAULT 3,\n  scheduled_at  TIMESTAMPTZ  NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),\n  started_at    TIMESTAMPTZ,\n  completed_at  TIMESTAMPTZ,\n  error         TEXT,\n  created_at    TIMESTAMPTZ  NOT NULL DEFAULT now()\n);\n```\n\n---\n\n### To Register a New Handler:\n\n1. **Add event type** to `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/event-types.ts`\n2. **Create handler file** (e.g., `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/handlers/my-handler.ts`) with factory function pattern\n3. **Register in index.ts** (line ~206) before worker starts\n4. **Emit events** from settlement code using `emitEvent(txDb.rawSql, EventTypes.MY_EVENT, payload)`\n5. **Test** using queue integration test pattern with handler mocking and DB assertions"}],"totalDurationMs":73177,"totalTokens":52126,"totalToolUseCount":28,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":411,"cache_read_input_tokens":49544,"output_tokens":2166,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemera