{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012uVnuaN6MtseZ8yLSM3NZr","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information needed. Let me create a comprehensive report.\n\n## Backend Service Architecture - Complete Analysis\n\nI've thoroughly explored the backend service architecture. Here's what you need to know:\n\n---\n\n### 1. Directory Structure\n\n```\n/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/\n├── queue/                          # Async event queue infrastructure\n│   ├── event-types.ts             # Event type constants\n│   ├── handler-registry.ts        # Handler registration map\n│   ├── emit-event.ts              # Event producer function\n│   ├── worker.ts                  # Event worker (polling consumer)\n│   ├── health.ts                  # Queue depth queries\n│   ├── handlers/\n│   │   └── referral-claim.ts      # Example: Claim handler\n│   ├── index.ts                   # Public exports\n│   └── __tests__/\n│\n├── worker/                         # Background workers (non-queue)\n│   ├── settlement.ts              # Polling-based settlement\n│   ├── settle-tx.ts               # Settlement logic\n│   ├── pda-watcher.ts             # WebSocket PDA monitoring\n│   ├── closecall-clock.ts         # Close Call round creation\n│   ├── retry.ts                   # Retry logic\n│   ├── account-decoder.ts         # Anchor account decoding\n│   └── pyth-poster.ts\n│\n├── routes/                         # HTTP route handlers\n├── middleware/                     # Auth, rate limiting\n├── db.ts                          # Database interface & implementation (62KB)\n├── db-config.ts                   # Connection config\n├── index.ts                       # Server startup (registers handlers)\n├── logger.ts\n├── config.ts\n└── ... (other files)\n\nMigrations: /workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/migrations/\n├── 001_init.sql\n├── 009_event_queue.sql            # Event queue schema\n├── 010_referral.sql\n└── ... (others)\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. Event Types\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/event-types.ts`\n\n```typescript\nexport const EventTypes = {\n  REFERRAL_CODE_APPLIED: \"referral.code_applied\",\n  REFERRAL_GAME_SETTLED: \"referral.game_settled\",\n  REFERRAL_CLAIM_REQUESTED: \"referral.claim_requested\",\n  GAME_SETTLED: \"game.settled\",\n  REWARD_POOL_FUND: \"reward.pool_fund\",\n  POINTS_GRANT: \"points.grant\",\n  CRATE_DROP: \"crate.drop\",\n  CRATE_SOL_PAYOUT: \"crate.sol_payout\",\n} as const;\n\nexport type EventType = (typeof EventTypes)[keyof typeof EventTypes];\n```\n\n**Pattern**: String constants defined in a const object, derived union type prevents typos at compile time.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Handler Registration Pattern\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/handler-registry.ts`\n\n```typescript\nexport type EventHandler = (\n  payload: Record<string, unknown>,\n) => Promise<void>;\n\nconst handlers = new Map<string, EventHandler>();\n\nexport function registerHandler(\n  eventType: EventType,\n  handler: EventHandler,\n): void {\n  handlers.set(eventType, handler);\n}\n\nexport function getHandler(eventType: string): EventHandler | undefined {\n  return handlers.get(eventType);\n}\n\nexport function clearHandlers(): void {\n  handlers.clear();\n}\n```\n\n**Key points**:\n- Handlers are stored in a Map\n- One handler per event type (no pub/sub fan-out in v1)\n- Handlers must be **idempotent** — re-processing is a safe no-op\n- Test isolation via `clearHandlers()`\n\n**Registration in index.ts** (lines 206-209):\n```typescript\nregisterHandler(\n  EventTypes.REFERRAL_CLAIM_REQUESTED,\n  createClaimHandler({ db, connection, serverKeypair: config.serverKeypair }),\n);\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. Event Queue Database Schema\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/migrations/009_event_queue.sql`\n\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE event_queue (\n  id            BIGINT GENERATED ALWAYS AS IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY,\n  event_type    TEXT         NOT NULL,\n  payload       JSONB        NOT NULL,\n  status        TEXT         NOT NULL DEFAULT 'pending' \n                CHECK (status IN ('pending', 'processing', 'completed', 'failed', 'dead')),\n  attempts      INTEGER      NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n  max_attempts  INTEGER      NOT NULL DEFAULT 3,\n  scheduled_at  TIMESTAMPTZ  NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),\n  started_at    TIMESTAMPTZ,\n  completed_at  TIMESTAMPTZ,\n  error         TEXT,\n  created_at    TIMESTAMPTZ  NOT NULL DEFAULT now()\n);\n\nCREATE INDEX idx_event_queue_poll ON event_queue (scheduled_at) \n  WHERE status = 'pending';\nCREATE INDEX idx_event_queue_status ON event_queue (status, created_at);\n```\n\n**Status transitions**:\n- `pending` → `processing` → `completed` (success)\n- `pending` → `processing` → `dead` (no handler registered)\n- `pending` → `processing` → `pending` (transient failure, retries with exponential backoff)\n- `pending` → `processing` → `dead` (permanent failure after max_attempts exceeded)\n\n---\n\n### 5. Event Emission Pattern\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/emit-event.ts`\n\n```typescript\nexport type SqlOrTransaction = postgres.Sql;\n\nexport interface EmitEventOptions {\n  maxAttempts?: number; // default: 3\n  scheduledAt?: Date; // default: now\n}\n\nexport async function emitEvent(\n  tx: SqlOrTransaction,\n  eventType: EventType,\n  payload: Record<string, unknown>,\n  options?: EmitEventOptions,\n): Promise<{ eventId: bigint }> {\n  const maxAttempts = options?.maxAttempts ?? 3;\n  const scheduledAt = options?.scheduledAt ?? new Date();\n\n  const rows = await tx<{ id: string }[]>`\n    INSERT INTO event_queue (event_type, payload, max_attempts, scheduled_at)\n    VALUES (${eventType}, ${tx.json(payload as postgres.JSONValue)}, ${maxAttempts}, ${scheduledAt})\n    RETURNING id\n  `;\n\n  return { eventId: BigInt(rows[0]!.id) };\n}\n```\n\n**Usage**: Called within a database transaction to atomically commit the event alongside the triggering operation.\n\n**Example from referral routes**:\n```typescript\nawait emitEvent(\n  tx as unknown as postgres.Sql,\n  EventTypes.REFERRAL_CLAIM_REQUESTED,\n  {\n    claimId: row.id,\n    userId: row.user_id,\n    wallet: row.wallet,\n    amountLamports: row.amount_lamports,\n    requestedAt: new Date().toISOString(),\n  },\n);\n```\n\n---\n\n### 6. Event Worker (Consumer)\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/worker.ts`\n\n```typescript\nexport function createEventWorker(\n  sql: postgres.Sql,\n  options?: EventWorkerOptions,\n): EventWorker {\n  // Polls every 1500ms (default)\n  // Batch size: 10 (default)\n}\n```\n\n**Worker lifecycle**:\n1. Polls `event_queue` table every `pollIntervalMs` (default: 1500ms)\n2. Claims batch of `pending` events with `FOR UPDATE SKIP LOCKED` (safe for concurrent workers)\n3. Sets status to `processing` and `started_at = now()`\n4. Looks up handler via `getHandler(event_type)`\n5. Executes handler with event payload\n6. On success: sets status → `completed`, `completed_at = now()`\n7. On failure:\n   - Increments `attempts`\n   - If `attempts >= max_attempts`: status → `dead`, logs \"MANUAL REVIEW NEEDED\"\n   - Else: status → `pending`, reschedules with exponential backoff (5s → 30s → 300s+)\n8. No handler registered: marks dead immediately, logs warning\n\n**Error handling flow**:\n- Transient errors (network, RPC timeout): retry with backoff\n- Permanent errors (invalid payload, business logic failure): marked `dead` for manual review\n- Handler throws: error caught, logged, retry scheduled\n\n---\n\n### 7. Handler Example: Referral Claim\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/handlers/referral-claim.ts`\n\n```typescript\nexport interface ClaimHandlerDeps {\n  db: Db;\n  connection: Connection;\n  serverKeypair: Keypair;\n}\n\nexport function createClaimHandler(deps: ClaimHandlerDeps) {\n  const { db, connection, serverKeypair } = deps;\n\n  return async (payload: Record<string, unknown>): Promise<void> => {\n    const claimId = payload.claimId as string;\n    const userId = payload.userId as string;\n    const wallet = payload.wallet as string;\n    const amountLamports = payload.amountLamports as string;\n\n    // Idempotency check: skip if already completed or permanently failed\n    const claim = await db.getReferralClaim(claimId);\n    if (claim?.status === \"completed\" || claim?.status === \"failed\") {\n      return; // safe no-op\n    }\n\n    // Update status to processing\n    await db.updateClaimStatus(claimId, \"processing\");\n\n    try {\n      // Re-verify balance (prevents overpay on concurrent claims)\n      const pending = BigInt(await db.getPendingBalanceByUserId(userId));\n      const amount = BigInt(amountLamports);\n      if (pending < amount) {\n        // Permanent failure\n        await db.updateClaimStatus(claimId, \"failed\", {\n          error: `Insufficient balance: pending=${pending}, claim=${amount}`,\n        });\n        return;\n      }\n\n      // Execute SOL transfer\n      const tx = new Transaction({...});\n      tx.add(SystemProgram.transfer({...}));\n      tx.sign(serverKeypair);\n      const txSignature = await connection.sendRawTransaction(...);\n      await connection.confirmTransaction(...);\n\n      // Record success\n      await db.updateClaimStatus(claimId, \"completed\", { txSignature });\n    } catch (err) {\n      // Transient error: increment retry count\n      const nextRetry = claim.retry_count + 1;\n      const isFinal = nextRetry >= MAX_CLAIM_RETRIES;\n      const nextStatus = isFinal ? \"failed\" : \"error\";\n\n      await db.updateClaimStatus(claimId, nextStatus, {\n        error: err.message,\n        incrementRetry: true,\n      });\n\n      if (!isFinal) {\n        throw err; // Queue worker will retry with backoff\n      }\n    }\n  };\n}\n```\n\n**Key patterns**:\n- **Idempotent**: skips if already completed or failed\n- **Partial success handling**: updates status through progression\n- **Transient vs permanent errors**: distinguishes between retryable and dead states\n- **Re-verification**: checks constraints again at handler time (concurrent claim prevention)\n\n---\n\n### 8. Database Interface (Db)\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/db.ts` (starting line 319)\n\nKey methods:\n\n```typescript\nexport interface Db {\n  // Rounds\n  insertRound(params: InsertRoundParams): Promise<Round>;\n  getRoundByPda(pda: string): Promise<Round | undefined>;\n  updateRoundPhase(pda: string, newPhase: RoundPhase, updates?: ...): Promise<Round>;\n  \n  // Transactions\n  insertTransaction(params: InsertTransactionParams): Promise<void>;\n  getTransactions(wallet: string, cursor?, limit?, game?): Promise<Transaction[]>;\n  \n  // Referral claims\n  getReferralClaim(claimId: string): Promise<ReferralClaim | undefined>;\n  updateClaimStatus(\n    claimId: string,\n    status: ReferralClaim[\"status\"],\n    meta?: { txSignature?: string; error?: string; incrementRetry?: boolean }\n  ): Promise<ReferralClaim>;\n  getPendingBalanceByUserId(userId: string): Promise<string>;\n  \n  // Player profiles\n  createPlayerProfile(wallet: string): Promise<PlayerProfile>;\n  getProfileByWallet(wallet: string): Promise<PlayerProfile | null>;\n  getProfileByUserId(userId: string): Promise<PlayerProfile | null>;\n  \n  // Game entries\n  upsertGameEntry(entry: GameEntryUpsert): Promise<void>;\n  upsertGameEntries(entries: GameEntryUpsert[]): Promise<void>;\n  getEntriesByRound(roundPda: string): Promise<GameEntry[]>;\n  \n  // Transactions\n  withTransaction<T>(fn: (db: Db) => Promise<T>): Promise<T>;\n  \n  // Raw SQL access for emitEvent()\n  readonly rawSql: any;\n  \n  close(): Promise<void>;\n}\n```\n\n**Transaction pattern** (`withTransaction`):\n```typescript\nawait db.withTransaction(async (txDb) => {\n  // All operations share same transaction\n  await txDb.insertGameEntries(...);\n  await emitEvent(txDb.rawSql, EventTypes.GAME_SETTLED, {...});\n  // Auto-commits on success, rolls back on error\n});\n```\n\n---\n\n### 9. Startup Initialization\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/index.ts` (lines 205-218)\n\n```typescript\n// Register event handlers BEFORE starting worker\nregisterHandler(\n  EventTypes.REFERRAL_CLAIM_REQUESTED,\n  createClaimHandler({ db, connection, serverKeypair: config.serverKeypair }),\n);\n\n// Start event queue worker\nconst eventWorker = createEventWorker(sql, {\n  pollIntervalMs: config.eventQueuePollMs,\n});\neventWorker.start();\nlogger.info(\"Event queue worker started\", {\n  pollIntervalMs: config.eventQueuePollMs,\n});\n```\n\n**Order matters**: Handlers registered before worker starts to avoid race conditions.\n\n---\n\n### 10. Existing Handler Files\n\n**Only one handler implemented so far**:\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/handlers/referral-claim.ts`\n\nThis is the complete referral claim fulfillment handler — the only side-effect currently wired into the event queue.\n\n---\n\n### Key Takeaways\n\n1. **Event-driven architecture**: Decouples game settlement hot path from side-effects\n2. **Handler pattern**: Pure function that accepts payload, is idempotent, throws on retryable errors\n3. **Transactional safety**: Events emitted within DB transactions for atomicity\n4. **Retry strategy**: Exponential backoff (5s → 30s → 300s) before permanent failure\n5. **Observability**: Failed events marked `dead` with error details for manual review\n6. **Concurrency**: `FOR UPDATE SKIP LOCKED` ensures safe multi-worker polling\n7. **Isolation**: `clearHandlers()` for test isolation\n\nThe system is production-ready but currently minimal — only the claim handler is registered. New handlers follow the same pattern: create a handler function file, export a factory, register it in index.ts before worker start."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f10eba72-1ffd-4ead-a08a-c9ca057b30d5","uuid":"87369666-194f-47cd-a915-3449d7240239","timestamp":"2026-04-03T19:29:57.761Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the backend service at /workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/ to understand:\n1. Directory structure — what directories exist under src/\n2. The event-types.ts file — what event types exist and their shape\n3. The queue/ directory — how event handlers are registered (the handler registry pattern)\n4. The db.ts file — the Db interface shape\n5. Any existing handler files in queue/ or worker/ to see their pattern\n\nBe thorough — I need to know the handler registration pattern and existing code patterns.","agentId":"a21ef4ba778308083","agentType":"Explore","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information needed. Let me create a comprehensive report.\n\n## Backend Service Architecture - Complete Analysis\n\nI've thoroughly explored the backend service architecture. Here's what you need to know:\n\n---\n\n### 1. Directory Structure\n\n```\n/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/\n├── queue/                          # Async event queue infrastructure\n│   ├── event-types.ts             # Event type constants\n│   ├── handler-registry.ts        # Handler registration map\n│   ├── emit-event.ts              # Event producer function\n│   ├── worker.ts                  # Event worker (polling consumer)\n│   ├── health.ts                  # Queue depth queries\n│   ├── handlers/\n│   │   └── referral-claim.ts      # Example: Claim handler\n│   ├── index.ts                   # Public exports\n│   └── __tests__/\n│\n├── worker/                         # Background workers (non-queue)\n│   ├── settlement.ts              # Polling-based settlement\n│   ├── settle-tx.ts               # Settlement logic\n│   ├── pda-watcher.ts             # WebSocket PDA monitoring\n│   ├── closecall-clock.ts         # Close Call round creation\n│   ├── retry.ts                   # Retry logic\n│   ├── account-decoder.ts         # Anchor account decoding\n│   └── pyth-poster.ts\n│\n├── routes/                         # HTTP route handlers\n├── middleware/                     # Auth, rate limiting\n├── db.ts                          # Database interface & implementation (62KB)\n├── db-config.ts                   # Connection config\n├── index.ts                       # Server startup (registers handlers)\n├── logger.ts\n├── config.ts\n└── ... (other files)\n\nMigrations: /workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/migrations/\n├── 001_init.sql\n├── 009_event_queue.sql            # Event queue schema\n├── 010_referral.sql\n└── ... (others)\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. Event Types\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/event-types.ts`\n\n```typescript\nexport const EventTypes = {\n  REFERRAL_CODE_APPLIED: \"referral.code_applied\",\n  REFERRAL_GAME_SETTLED: \"referral.game_settled\",\n  REFERRAL_CLAIM_REQUESTED: \"referral.claim_requested\",\n  GAME_SETTLED: \"game.settled\",\n  REWARD_POOL_FUND: \"reward.pool_fund\",\n  POINTS_GRANT: \"points.grant\",\n  CRATE_DROP: \"crate.drop\",\n  CRATE_SOL_PAYOUT: \"crate.sol_payout\",\n} as const;\n\nexport type EventType = (typeof EventTypes)[keyof typeof EventTypes];\n```\n\n**Pattern**: String constants defined in a const object, derived union type prevents typos at compile time.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Handler Registration Pattern\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/handler-registry.ts`\n\n```typescript\nexport type EventHandler = (\n  payload: Record<string, unknown>,\n) => Promise<void>;\n\nconst handlers = new Map<string, EventHandler>();\n\nexport function registerHandler(\n  eventType: EventType,\n  handler: EventHandler,\n): void {\n  handlers.set(eventType, handler);\n}\n\nexport function getHandler(eventType: string): EventHandler | undefined {\n  return handlers.get(eventType);\n}\n\nexport function clearHandlers(): void {\n  handlers.clear();\n}\n```\n\n**Key points**:\n- Handlers are stored in a Map\n- One handler per event type (no pub/sub fan-out in v1)\n- Handlers must be **idempotent** — re-processing is a safe no-op\n- Test isolation via `clearHandlers()`\n\n**Registration in index.ts** (lines 206-209):\n```typescript\nregisterHandler(\n  EventTypes.REFERRAL_CLAIM_REQUESTED,\n  createClaimHandler({ db, connection, serverKeypair: config.serverKeypair }),\n);\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. Event Queue Database Schema\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/migrations/009_event_queue.sql`\n\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE event_queue (\n  id            BIGINT GENERATED ALWAYS AS IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY,\n  event_type    TEXT         NOT NULL,\n  payload       JSONB        NOT NULL,\n  status        TEXT         NOT NULL DEFAULT 'pending' \n                CHECK (status IN ('pending', 'processing', 'completed', 'failed', 'dead')),\n  attempts      INTEGER      NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n  max_attempts  INTEGER      NOT NULL DEFAULT 3,\n  scheduled_at  TIMESTAMPTZ  NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),\n  started_at    TIMESTAMPTZ,\n  completed_at  TIMESTAMPTZ,\n  error         TEXT,\n  created_at    TIMESTAMPTZ  NOT NULL DEFAULT now()\n);\n\nCREATE INDEX idx_event_queue_poll ON event_queue (scheduled_at) \n  WHERE status = 'pending';\nCREATE INDEX idx_event_queue_status ON event_queue (status, created_at);\n```\n\n**Status transitions**:\n- `pending` → `processing` → `completed` (success)\n- `pending` → `processing` → `dead` (no handler registered)\n- `pending` → `processing` → `pending` (transient failure, retries with exponential backoff)\n- `pending` → `processing` → `dead` (permanent failure after max_attempts exceeded)\n\n---\n\n### 5. Event Emission Pattern\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/emit-event.ts`\n\n```typescript\nexport type SqlOrTransaction = postgres.Sql;\n\nexport interface EmitEventOptions {\n  maxAttempts?: number; // default: 3\n  scheduledAt?: Date; // default: now\n}\n\nexport async function emitEvent(\n  tx: SqlOrTransaction,\n  eventType: EventType,\n  payload: Record<string, unknown>,\n  options?: EmitEventOptions,\n): Promise<{ eventId: bigint }> {\n  const maxAttempts = options?.maxAttempts ?? 3;\n  const scheduledAt = options?.scheduledAt ?? new Date();\n\n  const rows = await tx<{ id: string }[]>`\n    INSERT INTO event_queue (event_type, payload, max_attempts, scheduled_at)\n    VALUES (${eventType}, ${tx.json(payload as postgres.JSONValue)}, ${maxAttempts}, ${scheduledAt})\n    RETURNING id\n  `;\n\n  return { eventId: BigInt(rows[0]!.id) };\n}\n```\n\n**Usage**: Called within a database transaction to atomically commit the event alongside the triggering operation.\n\n**Example from referral routes**:\n```typescript\nawait emitEvent(\n  tx as unknown as postgres.Sql,\n  EventTypes.REFERRAL_CLAIM_REQUESTED,\n  {\n    claimId: row.id,\n    userId: row.user_id,\n    wallet: row.wallet,\n    amountLamports: row.amount_lamports,\n    requestedAt: new Date().toISOString(),\n  },\n);\n```\n\n---\n\n### 6. Event Worker (Consumer)\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/worker.ts`\n\n```typescript\nexport function createEventWorker(\n  sql: postgres.Sql,\n  options?: EventWorkerOptions,\n): EventWorker {\n  // Polls every 1500ms (default)\n  // Batch size: 10 (default)\n}\n```\n\n**Worker lifecycle**:\n1. Polls `event_queue` table every `pollIntervalMs` (default: 1500ms)\n2. Claims batch of `pending` events with `FOR UPDATE SKIP LOCKED` (safe for concurrent workers)\n3. Sets status to `processing` and `started_at = now()`\n4. Looks up handler via `getHandler(event_type)`\n5. Executes handler with event payload\n6. On success: sets status → `completed`, `completed_at = now()`\n7. On failure:\n   - Increments `attempts`\n   - If `attempts >= max_attempts`: status → `dead`, logs \"MANUAL REVIEW NEEDED\"\n   - Else: status → `pending`, reschedules with exponential backoff (5s → 30s → 300s+)\n8. No handler registered: marks dead immediately, logs warning\n\n**Error handling flow**:\n- Transient errors (network, RPC timeout): retry with backoff\n- Permanent errors (invalid payload, business logic failure): marked `dead` for manual review\n- Handler throws: error caught, logged, retry scheduled\n\n---\n\n### 7. Handler Example: Referral Claim\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/handlers/referral-claim.ts`\n\n```typescript\nexport interface ClaimHandlerDeps {\n  db: Db;\n  connection: Connection;\n  serverKeypair: Keypair;\n}\n\nexport function createClaimHandler(deps: ClaimHandlerDeps) {\n  const { db, connection, serverKeypair } = deps;\n\n  return async (payload: Record<string, unknown>): Promise<void> => {\n    const claimId = payload.claimId as string;\n    const userId = payload.userId as string;\n    const wallet = payload.wallet as string;\n    const amountLamports = payload.amountLamports as string;\n\n    // Idempotency check: skip if already completed or permanently failed\n    const claim = await db.getReferralClaim(claimId);\n    if (claim?.status === \"completed\" || claim?.status === \"failed\") {\n      return; // safe no-op\n    }\n\n    // Update status to processing\n    await db.updateClaimStatus(claimId, \"processing\");\n\n    try {\n      // Re-verify balance (prevents overpay on concurrent claims)\n      const pending = BigInt(await db.getPendingBalanceByUserId(userId));\n      const amount = BigInt(amountLamports);\n      if (pending < amount) {\n        // Permanent failure\n        await db.updateClaimStatus(claimId, \"failed\", {\n          error: `Insufficient balance: pending=${pending}, claim=${amount}`,\n        });\n        return;\n      }\n\n      // Execute SOL transfer\n      const tx = new Transaction({...});\n      tx.add(SystemProgram.transfer({...}));\n      tx.sign(serverKeypair);\n      const txSignature = await connection.sendRawTransaction(...);\n      await connection.confirmTransaction(...);\n\n      // Record success\n      await db.updateClaimStatus(claimId, \"completed\", { txSignature });\n    } catch (err) {\n      // Transient error: increment retry count\n      const nextRetry = claim.retry_count + 1;\n      const isFinal = nextRetry >= MAX_CLAIM_RETRIES;\n      const nextStatus = isFinal ? \"failed\" : \"error\";\n\n      await db.updateClaimStatus(claimId, nextStatus, {\n        error: err.message,\n        incrementRetry: true,\n      });\n\n      if (!isFinal) {\n        throw err; // Queue worker will retry with backoff\n      }\n    }\n  };\n}\n```\n\n**Key patterns**:\n- **Idempotent**: skips if already completed or failed\n- **Partial success handling**: updates status through progression\n- **Transient vs permanent errors**: distinguishes between retryable and dead states\n- **Re-verification**: checks constraints again at handler time (concurrent claim prevention)\n\n---\n\n### 8. Database Interface (Db)\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/db.ts` (starting line 319)\n\nKey methods:\n\n```typescript\nexport interface Db {\n  // Rounds\n  insertRound(params: InsertRoundParams): Promise<Round>;\n  getRoundByPda(pda: string): Promise<Round | undefined>;\n  updateRoundPhase(pda: string, newPhase: RoundPhase, updates?: ...): Promise<Round>;\n  \n  // Transactions\n  insertTransaction(params: InsertTransactionParams): Promise<void>;\n  getTransactions(wallet: string, cursor?, limit?, game?): Promise<Transaction[]>;\n  \n  // Referral claims\n  getReferralClaim(claimId: string): Promise<ReferralClaim | undefined>;\n  updateClaimStatus(\n    claimId: string,\n    status: ReferralClaim[\"status\"],\n    meta?: { txSignature?: string; error?: string; incrementRetry?: boolean }\n  ): Promise<ReferralClaim>;\n  getPendingBalanceByUserId(userId: string): Promise<string>;\n  \n  // Player profiles\n  createPlayerProfile(wallet: string): Promise<PlayerProfile>;\n  getProfileByWallet(wallet: string): Promise<PlayerProfile | null>;\n  getProfileByUserId(userId: string): Promise<PlayerProfile | null>;\n  \n  // Game entries\n  upsertGameEntry(entry: GameEntryUpsert): Promise<void>;\n  upsertGameEntries(entries: GameEntryUpsert[]): Promise<void>;\n  getEntriesByRound(roundPda: string): Promise<GameEntry[]>;\n  \n  // Transactions\n  withTransaction<T>(fn: (db: Db) => Promise<T>): Promise<T>;\n  \n  // Raw SQL access for emitEvent()\n  readonly rawSql: any;\n  \n  close(): Promise<void>;\n}\n```\n\n**Transaction pattern** (`withTransaction`):\n```typescript\nawait db.withTransaction(async (txDb) => {\n  // All operations share same transaction\n  await txDb.insertGameEntries(...);\n  await emitEvent(txDb.rawSql, EventTypes.GAME_SETTLED, {...});\n  // Auto-commits on success, rolls back on error\n});\n```\n\n---\n\n### 9. Startup Initialization\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/index.ts` (lines 205-218)\n\n```typescript\n// Register event handlers BEFORE starting worker\nregisterHandler(\n  EventTypes.REFERRAL_CLAIM_REQUESTED,\n  createClaimHandler({ db, connection, serverKeypair: config.serverKeypair }),\n);\n\n// Start event queue worker\nconst eventWorker = createEventWorker(sql, {\n  pollIntervalMs: config.eventQueuePollMs,\n});\neventWorker.start();\nlogger.info(\"Event queue worker started\", {\n  pollIntervalMs: config.eventQueuePollMs,\n});\n```\n\n**Order matters**: Handlers registered before worker starts to avoid race conditions.\n\n---\n\n### 10. Existing Handler Files\n\n**Only one handler implemented so far**:\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/handlers/referral-claim.ts`\n\nThis is the complete referral claim fulfillment handler — the only side-effect currently wired into the event queue.\n\n---\n\n### Key Takeaways\n\n1. **Event-driven architecture**: Decouples game settlement hot path from side-effects\n2. **Handler pattern**: Pure function that accepts payload, is idempotent, throws on retryable errors\n3. **Transactional safety**: Events emitted within DB transactions for atomicity\n4. **Retry strategy**: Exponential backoff (5s → 30s → 300s) before permanent failure\n5. **Observability**: Failed events marked `dead` with error details for manual review\n6. **Concurrency**: `FOR UPDATE SKIP LOCKED` ensures safe multi-worker polling\n7. **Isolation**: `clearHandlers()` for test isolation\n\nThe system is production-ready but currently minimal — only the claim handler is registered. New handlers follow the same pattern: create a handler function file, export a factory, register it in index.ts before worker start."}],"totalDurationMs":90877,"totalTokens":59632,"totalToolUseCount":27,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":537,"cache_read_input_tokens":55138,"output_tokens":3956,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":537},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
